model.world

Class Room

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.world.Room
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ChestRoom, FoeRoom, TrapRoom

    public class Room
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the room management of the system. These rooms are link thanks to Door.

    • Method Detail

      • link

        public void link(Direction direction,
                 Room room)
        This method is for link a door with a other room. The door is create in the Direction in parameter. And the room in parameter will got a door for go back in the opposite direction (Direction.getOpposite()).
        Parameters:
        direction - The door is create in this direction
        room - This room will got a door in the opposite direction
        See Also:
        Door

      • link

        public void link(Direction direction,
                 Room room,
                 KeyColor keyColor)
        This method is the same like link(Direction, Room). But the door will be lock with the lock color (KeyColor) pass in parameter.
        Parameters:
        direction - The door is create in this direction
        room - This room will got a door in the opposite direction
        keyColor - The color of the lock on the door
        See Also:
        LockedDoor, KeyColor, Key

      • link

        private void link(Door door,
                  Room room)
        Private method for link two room with one Door/LockedDoor. The method is call by link(Direction, Room) or link(Direction, Room, KeyColor)
        Parameters:
        door - The door to add to rooms
        room - This room will got a door in the opposite direction

      • forward

        public void forward(Dungeon dungeonInstance,
                    Direction direction)
        This method is for forward the player in the Direction pass in parameter. If there is no door in this room in this Direction, this method do nothing. If the door is lock (LockedDoor) and the Player got the key, the player can chose if he wants to use his Key on this LockedDoor for unlock it.
        Parameters:
        dungeonInstance - Dungeon where the player is in.
        direction - Direction where the player wants to go.

      • getDoor

        public Door getDoor(Direction direction)
        This function is for get the Door in this room on the Direction in parameter.
        Parameters:
        direction - Direction where you want the door.
        Returns:
        The Door if exists in this Direction. If there is no door in this Direction return null

      • printRoom

        public void printRoom()
        Print the direction where there is a Door in the room to the player console.

      • setChest

        public ChestRoom setChest(Equipment inChest)
        Convert this room to a ChestRoom. Used by random generator (DungeonGenerator.generate())
        Parameters:
        inChest - The item in the chest.
        Returns:
        The new room to use. If the old rooms was linked, this room got same links.
